  "helpStepLoginTitle": "Create account & sign in",
  "helpStepLoginDesc": "Sign up with email or sign in with Google/Apple. Confirm your email via the link if asked, then you're ready to start.",
  "helpStepWorkspaceTitle": "Set up a workspace",
  "helpStepWorkspaceDesc": "On first sign-in a workspace is created for you automatically. From the workspace menu in the top-right you can create more workspaces or invite members.",
  "helpStepInboxTitle": "Connect your mailbox",
  "helpStepInboxDesc": "Attach your order mailbox (Gmail/Outlook/IONOS) under Settings → Mailbox. Order confirmations, shipping and delivery mails will then be detected automatically.",
  "helpStepInventoryTitle": "Maintain inventory",
  "helpStepInventoryDesc": "In the Inventory tab add items with stock count and minimum stock level. Sold items are removed from stock automatically and surface in the \"Sold\" tab.",

  "helpInboxSection": "Mailbox (email import)",
  "helpInboxIntro": "The app reads your mailbox via IMAP, detects order confirmations and shipping mails and proposes them as deals. No mail is ever sent.",
  "helpInboxGmailTitle": "Connect Gmail / Google Workspace",
  "helpInboxGmailDesc": "Gmail does not allow login with your normal password. You need an app password:\n• Enable two-factor authentication at myaccount.google.com → Security.\n• Open myaccount.google.com/apppasswords, name it (e.g. \"Inventory app\") and copy the 16-character app password.\n• In the app: Settings → Mailbox → IMAP server \"imap.gmail.com\", port 993, SSL, username = your mail, password = the app password.",
  "helpInboxOutlookTitle": "Connect Outlook.com / Microsoft 365",
  "helpInboxOutlookDesc": "Outlook and Microsoft 365 also use app passwords:\n• Sign in to account.microsoft.com → Security → Advanced security options → create an app password.\n• In the app: IMAP server \"outlook.office365.com\", port 993, SSL, username = your mail, password = the app password.\n• Note: school/work tenants often require admin approval first.",
  "helpInboxIonosTitle": "Connect IONOS / 1&1",
  "helpInboxIonosDesc": "IONOS supports the regular mail login directly:\n• IMAP server \"imap.ionos.de\" (or \".com\" depending on region), port 993, SSL.\n• Username = full mail address, password = your mailbox password.\n• If login fails: in IONOS Webmail under \"Settings → Security\" check whether IMAP is enabled.",
  "helpInboxTabsTitle": "The three inbox tabs",
  "helpInboxTabsDesc": "Incoming mails land in three tabs depending on how confidently the app can classify them.",
  "helpInboxTabSuggestions": "Suggestions — order confirmations not yet linked to a deal. Tap a mail, review the parsed fields, accept it as a new deal.",
  "helpInboxTabUpdated": "Updated — mails that change an existing deal (e.g. shipping update, cancellation). Here you see what the pipeline applied automatically.",
  "helpInboxTabUnclassified": "Unclassified — mails the app could not assign confidently. You can link them to a deal manually or mark them irrelevant.",
  "helpInboxWhitelistTitle": "Why don't I see some mails?",
  "helpInboxWhitelistDesc": "The app only reads mails from known shops/carriers (whitelist). Marketing newsletters, personal mail and unknown senders are ignored. If a shop is missing, report it via \"Report issues\" — new adapters are added server-side.",

  "helpDealsSection": "Deals",
  "helpDealsStatusFlow": "Each deal goes through five statuses — you can advance it manually or the mail pipeline does it for you.",
  "helpDealsStatusOrdered": "Ordered — the deal is created but not yet shipped. Set this once you have placed the order.",
  "helpDealsStatusInTransit": "In transit — shipping confirmation detected or set manually. Tracking number is polled every few hours.",
  "helpDealsStatusArrived": "Arrived — the carrier reports delivery to the sender (you). The item is ready to be listed/shipped onward.",
  "helpDealsStatusSold": "Sold — buyer is set, sales price recorded. The deal now counts toward statistics.",
  "helpDealsStatusDelivered": "Delivered — end customer received the item. Final status, deal is closed.",
  "helpDealsTrackingTitle": "Auto-tracking from mails",
  "helpDealsTrackingDesc": "When a shipping mail with a tracking number arrives (Amazon, DHL, DPD, UPS, Hermes, GLS), the matching deal is set to \"In transit\" automatically. Once the carrier reports delivery, the deal flips to \"Arrived\".",
  "helpDealsDropShipTitle": "Multi drop-ship",
  "helpDealsDropShipDesc": "If a deal sources from several shops (drop-ship), you can record multiple sources with their purchase prices when creating it. Profit is summed across sources, but the statistic counts the deal as one sale.",
  "helpDealsRetrackTitle": "Refresh shipment status now (Retrack)",
  "helpDealsRetrackDesc": "In the deal detail view, next to the tracking number, you'll find a refresh icon labelled \"Refresh status\". It asks the carrier for the current status right away instead of waiting for the next scheduled poll — handy, for example, just before a planned delivery.\nOne retrack per deal is allowed every 30 seconds. While the lock is active the button is greyed out and shows \"Please wait 30s\" — that protects the carrier API from unnecessary calls and you from rate limits.",

  "helpShippingSection": "Shipping & carrier API keys",
  "helpShippingIntroTitle": "Why carrier API keys?",
  "helpShippingIntroDesc": "So the app can fetch the live status of your shipments straight from the carrier (rather than just reading mails), you store one API key per carrier under Settings → Shipping. One key per carrier per workspace is enough — every member benefits from it.",
  "helpShippingDhlTitle": "DHL — actively supported",
  "helpShippingDhlDesc": "DHL works out of the box:\n• Create an account on developer.dhl.com (free).\n• Subscribe to the \"Shipment Tracking - Unified\" API there — the free tier is enough for personal use.\n• Copy the API key and paste it under Settings → Shipping → DHL → \"Save API key\".\nFrom now on, deals with a DHL tracking number are refreshed at regular intervals and the status (in transit, out for delivery, delivered) appears directly on the deal.",
  "helpShippingComingSoonTitle": "DPD and UPS — coming soon",
  "helpShippingComingSoonDesc": "DPD and UPS show up in the list but are currently marked \"Coming soon\" and not editable. The integration ships in a later update — until then, shipments from these carriers are still detected from shipping mails, only the live status is missing. Nothing is broken, this is intentional.",
  "helpShippingKeySafetyTitle": "What happens to my API key?",
  "helpShippingKeySafetyDesc": "The plaintext key leaves your device exactly once, when you save it, and is then stored encrypted on the server. In the app you only see the last four characters afterwards, e.g. \"••••••••a1b2\". You can replace or delete the key at any time — deleting it pauses the automatic status polls for that carrier.",

  "helpInventorySection": "Inventory",
  "helpInventoryAddTitle": "Add an item",
  "helpInventoryAddDesc": "Inventory tab → \"Add item\". Required: name + quantity. Optional: purchase price, minimum stock, sales channel, photo. For multiple units of the same item, increase the quantity instead of creating a new entry.",
  "helpInventoryStockTitle": "Update quantities",
  "helpInventoryStockDesc": "Tap an item and use the +/- buttons, or edit the quantity field directly. On a sale the quantity is decreased automatically when you pick the item in the deal form.",
  "helpInventoryMinStockTitle": "Minimum stock & warnings",
  "helpInventoryMinStockDesc": "Set a minimum stock per item (e.g. 2). Once the quantity drops below it, a yellow warning appears on the dashboard and inventory tab — and optionally a push notification.",
  "helpInventorySoldTabTitle": "Sold tab",
  "helpInventorySoldTabDesc": "Sold items disappear from stock and surface in the \"Sold\" tab. There you see buyer, sales price and profit per unit, filterable by date and buyer.",
  "helpInventoryStockValueTitle": "Stock value calculation",
  "helpInventoryStockValueDesc": "The stock value at the top of the tab sums (quantity × purchase price) across items with a purchase price. Items without a purchase price contribute 0 — please backfill them, otherwise the statistic is off.",

  "helpEntitiesSection": "Buyers, shops & suppliers",
  "helpEntitiesBuyersTitle": "Buyers",
  "helpEntitiesBuyersDesc": "People or platforms you sell to (e.g. \"Tobias\", \"eBay-Kleinanzeigen\", \"Vinted\"). Required-ish in the deal form — without a buyer there is no sale.",
  "helpEntitiesShopsTitle": "Shops",
  "helpEntitiesShopsDesc": "Online/offline sources you buy from (e.g. \"Amazon\", \"Saturn\", \"Otto\"). On shipping mails the app maps the mail to the matching shop automatically if the adapter recognises the sender.",
  "helpEntitiesSuppliersTitle": "Suppliers",
  "helpEntitiesSuppliersDesc": "Special case for B2B sources with payment terms (Net 30, Net 60). Suppliers live in their own tab and are linked to deals as a source — the due-date statistic then shows open balances.",
  "helpEntitiesBuyerColorTitle": "Buyer colour coding",
  "helpEntitiesBuyerColorDesc": "Each buyer can be assigned a colour (buyer card → pick colour). The colour appears in the deal table and statistics so you can see who a deal went to at a glance.",

  "helpTicketsSection": "Tickets",
  "helpTicketsWhatTitle": "What is a ticket?",
  "helpTicketsWhatDesc": "A ticket bundles several deals that go to the same buyer together — e.g. a bulk order with five items. The ticket sees the total price, all tracking numbers and a single shipping status.",
  "helpTicketsArchiveTitle": "Active vs archive",
  "helpTicketsArchiveDesc": "Active tickets are not yet closed. Once all deals in a ticket are at \"Delivered\", you can archive it — it disappears from the main view but remains in statistics.",

  "helpStatsSection": "Statistics",
  "helpStatsKpiTitle": "KPI cards",
  "helpStatsKpiDesc": "At the top you see revenue, profit, deal count and cashflow for the chosen range. Tap a card to jump to its detail view.",
  "helpStatsChartsTitle": "Charts",
  "helpStatsChartsDesc": "Line chart for revenue/profit over time, bar chart for top buyers and shops. Tap a bar to filter by that buyer/shop.",
  "helpStatsFiltersTitle": "Filters (buyer/shop/date)",
  "helpStatsFiltersDesc": "Use the filter icon at the top right to combine buyer, shop and date range. Filters are applied to all cards and charts in sync.",
  "helpStatsTaxTitle": "Tax / VAT reports",
  "helpStatsTaxDesc": "Statistics → \"Tax\" tab shows quarterly revenue + a VAT estimate (small business or standard regime). CSV export per quarter via the download icon. The estimate does not replace tax advice.",

  "helpWorkspaceSection": "Workspace & team",
  "helpWorkspaceWhatTitle": "What is a workspace?",
  "helpWorkspaceWhatDesc": "A workspace is an isolated data container — every deal, buyer, shop and inventory item belongs to exactly one workspace. You can keep multiple workspaces in parallel (e.g. \"Personal\" and \"Business\").",
  "helpWorkspaceInviteTitle": "Invite members",
  "helpWorkspaceInviteDesc": "Settings → Team → \"Invite member\". Provide a mail address and a role. The invitee receives a mail with a link; once they sign up the workspace appears on their side.",
  "helpWorkspaceRolesTitle": "Roles",
  "helpWorkspaceRoleOwner": "Owner — can do everything, including deleting the workspace, removing members and changing the plan.",
  "helpWorkspaceRoleAdmin": "Admin — read/write access, can invite members and manage carrier keys. Cannot delete the workspace.",
  "helpWorkspaceRoleMember": "Member — read/write access but cannot change team or carrier settings.",
  "helpWorkspacePricingTitle": "Pricing tier limits",
  "helpWorkspacePricingDesc": "Free, Pro and Business mainly differ in number of members, number of mailboxes and whether carrier polling is active. Current limits are on the pricing screen.",

  "helpPushSection": "Push notifications",
  "helpPushIosTitle": "Enable on iOS",
  "helpPushIosDesc": "On first launch iOS asks whether the app may send notifications — confirm with \"Allow\". If you declined: iOS Settings → Notifications → Inventory app → Allow notifications.",
  "helpPushAndroidTitle": "Enable on Android",
  "helpPushAndroidDesc": "Android 13+ asks explicitly for push permission. If you declined: Android Settings → Apps → Inventory app → Notifications → enable.",
  "helpPushWhenTitle": "When are pushes sent?",
  "helpPushWhenDesc": "• New order confirmation in the mailbox\n• Tracking update (shipped / arrived)\n• Minimum stock undercut (if enabled)\n• Workspace invitation\nYou can disable individual categories under Settings → Push.",

  "helpFaqSection": "Frequently asked questions (FAQ)",
  "helpFaqQ1": "Why don't I see any mails after adding the mailbox?",
  "helpFaqA1": "The first sync runs in the background and can take 1–10 minutes depending on mailbox size. Also, only mails from known shops/carriers are imported — marketing and personal mails are ignored.",
  "helpFaqQ2": "How do I change the language?",
  "helpFaqA2": "Settings → General → Language. Available right now: German, English. The change is applied immediately.",
  "helpFaqQ3": "How do I delete my data?",
  "helpFaqA3": "Settings → General → \"Delete account\". You must type the word DELETE to confirm. Account, workspaces and mailbox configuration are deleted immediately; mail metadata and stored images are removed from the database and storage within 30 days.",
  "helpFaqQ4": "What happens if I downgrade?",
  "helpFaqA4": "Existing data is preserved. Features above the downgrade limit (e.g. extra members, carrier polling) are paused until you upgrade again or actively reduce below the limit.",
  "helpFaqQ5": "How do I reset my password?",
  "helpFaqA5": "Login screen → \"Forgot password\". Enter your mail, you'll receive a reset link. Tapping the link opens the app and lets you set a new password.",
  "helpFaqQ6": "Why is my stock value wrong?",
  "helpFaqA6": "The stock value only counts items with a recorded purchase price. Open the inventory tab and filter for \"Without purchase price\" — backfill the missing values and the total will match.",
  "helpFaqQ7": "Tracking is not updating — what now?",
  "helpFaqA7": "Carrier polling runs every 4 hours. Check Settings → Shipping that the carrier API key is set. Without a key the app cannot query the status — the mail pipeline may fill the gap via shipping mails.",
  "helpFaqQ8": "Can I use multiple workspaces?",
  "helpFaqA8": "Yes. Tap the workspace name top-right → \"New workspace\". Switch with one tap; data is strictly isolated.",
  "helpFaqQ9": "Discord buttons are missing on a deal — why?",
  "helpFaqA9": "Buttons only appear if the buyer has at least one Discord server ID configured. Settings → Buyers → edit buyer → add Discord server IDs.",
  "helpFaqQ10": "How do I export my data as CSV?",
  "helpFaqA10": "Statistics → Tax tab → download icon (per quarter). A full data export is in preparation — until then please request it via \"Report issues\".",
  "helpFaqQ11": "How do I create a tax report?",
  "helpFaqA11": "Statistics → Tax tab → pick a quarter → download CSV. The app shows gross, net and VAT share; the breakdown depends on your tax regime (small business or standard).",
  "helpFaqQ12": "How do I enable dark mode?",
  "helpFaqA12": "Settings → General → Theme → \"Dark\". Optionally \"System\" — then it follows the iOS/Android system setting.",
  "helpFaqQ13": "Can I temporarily disable my account?",
  "helpFaqA13": "Not directly — there is only \"Delete account\". To pause push and mail sync: remove the mailbox in settings and disable push categories. Data stays as-is.",
  "helpFaqQ14": "How do I disable push notifications?",
  "helpFaqA14": "Either per category in Settings → Push, or completely via OS settings (iOS Notifications / Android notifications → Inventory app).",
  "helpFaqQ15": "How do I search inside the inbox?",
  "helpFaqA15": "Inbox tab → search icon top-right. You can search by sender, subject or tracking number. The search filters all three tabs (Suggestions / Updated / Unclassified) at the same time.",
  "helpFaqQ16": "Why don't I see deals from other members?",
  "helpFaqA16": "You may be in the wrong workspace. Check the workspace name top-right and switch if needed. Filters (buyer/shop/date) can also hide deals — clear them with the \"Clear filters\" button.",
  "helpFaqQ17": "What does the \"Review\" badge on a shipment mean?",
  "helpFaqA17": "The app has stored a tracking value, but our new detector isn't sure it really is a valid tracking number (e.g. because it comes from an older mail with an unclear format). Tap the deal and check the tracking card: \"Accept\" confirms the value, \"Dismiss\" clears it. On the deals list, the \"Review\" chip filters all affected deals at once.",
  "helpFaqQ18": "How does \"Re-evaluate tracking numbers\" in Settings work?",
  "helpFaqA18": "Settings → General → \"Re-evaluate tracking numbers\" rechecks every stored mail in this workspace with the latest, stricter detector. Wrongly stored values get flagged as \"Review\", newly recognised real trackings replace empty entries. Manually entered tracking numbers stay untouched. To protect against runaway loops, this runs at most once every 5 minutes per workspace.",
  "helpFaqQ19": "Why is a tracking number sometimes empty even though the shipping mail is there?",
  "helpFaqA19": "Since May 2026 the app only stores a tracking number when it is structurally verified (carrier pattern + length/checksum check). When the mail only contains an internal shop ID (e.g. an Amazon Logistics shipment ID) or the number is ambiguously formatted, the app deliberately leaves the field empty instead of saving a wrong value. You can always enter the tracking number manually on the deal — manual entries are never overwritten automatically.",

  "helpTroubleSection": "Troubleshooting",
  "helpTroubleConnectionTitle": "\"No connection to server\"",
  "helpTroubleConnectionDesc": "Check your internet connection and try \"Refresh\" (pull-to-refresh). If the issue persists: check the status page on the website, wait a few minutes — Supabase restarts can take a moment.",
  "helpTroubleImapAuthTitle": "\"IMAP login failed\"",
  "helpTroubleImapAuthDesc": "For Gmail/Outlook: make sure you use an app password, not your normal login password. For IONOS check that IMAP is enabled server-side. Typos in the server hostname are the most common cause.",
  "helpTroubleSyncStuckTitle": "Mailbox sync is stuck",
  "helpTroubleSyncStuckDesc": "Settings → Mailbox → select mailbox → \"Re-sync\". If still no mails arrive: remove the mailbox and re-add it — the bootstrap pump will then re-fetch all mails from the past 60 days.",
  "helpTroubleNotifMissingTitle": "Push notifications don't arrive",
  "helpTroubleNotifMissingDesc": "First check the OS notification settings (iOS Notifications / Android notifications → Inventory app → notifications allowed?). Then in the app under Settings → Push verify the individual categories are enabled. If everything is set to \"allowed\" and still nothing arrives, sign out and back in — that re-registers the push token.",
  "helpTroubleStatsEmptyTitle": "Statistics are empty",
  "helpTroubleStatsEmptyDesc": "Statistics only count deals with status \"Sold\" or \"Delivered\" and a sales price > 0. Check your date filter (top right) — it may be set to an empty range.",
  "helpTroubleLoginFailedTitle": "Login does not work",
  "helpTroubleLoginFailedDesc": "Make sure your mail is confirmed (link from welcome mail). For Google/Apple sign-in: help the app open the browser tab — some in-app browsers block the callback. Worst case, reset the password.",
  "helpTroubleUploadFailedTitle": "Photo upload fails",
  "helpTroubleUploadFailedDesc": "Images larger than 10 MB are rejected. Reduce size/quality, or grant the app access to photos/media library in OS settings. On a very slow connection upload can time out after 60 s — retry.",
  "helpTroubleSlowTitle": "App is suddenly slow",
  "helpTroubleSlowDesc": "Very long deal/inbox lists? Apply filters (date, status, buyer) to reduce render load. Fully quitting and restarting the app clears volatile in-memory caches. On older devices, archiving old tickets also helps.",
  "helpTroubleCarrierSetupTitle": "\"Setup incomplete: master key not configured\"",
  "helpTroubleCarrierSetupDesc": "This message appears when you try to save a carrier API key but the backend has no master key to encrypt it with. It's not a problem with your account but a one-off backend setup step:\n• Hosted setup (regular users): wait a moment and try again — we set the master key centrally, usually within a few hours.\n• Self-hoster / Supabase admin: migration `20260516000000_carrier_master_key_bootstrap.sql` must be applied and the `CARRIER_MASTER_KEY` secret has to be set at the Supabase project level. Admin details live in the repo at `supabase/functions/tracking-poll/SETUP.md`.\nUntil it's fixed you can keep updating shipments manually — only the automatic per-carrier live status is paused.",

  "helpPrivacySection": "Privacy & contact",
  "helpPrivacyDataTitle": "What data is stored?",
  "helpPrivacyDataDesc": "What is stored: master data (workspace, deals, buyers), mailbox config (password encrypted) and photo uploads. From parsed mails we store headers (sender, subject, date) and a normalised JSON extract (order ID, tracking number, totals, product); the full mail body is not retained. Mail metadata is auto-deleted after 100 days. Details in the privacy policy under Settings → General.",
  "helpPrivacySupportTitle": "How do I reach support?",
  "helpPrivacySupportDesc": "\"Report issues\" generates a mail with app version, OS and workspace ID (no passwords). Reply time usually < 48 h.",
  "helpPrivacyNoteTitle": "Important notes",
  "helpPrivacyNoteDesc": "The app does not replace bookkeeping or tax advice — statistics are estimates. Before your first quarterly close please consult a tax advisor.",

